&lt;p>&lt;strong>Part 2 of the &lt;em>Human Skills, AI-Expanded&lt;/em> series&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Program directors and PMO leads live in the gap between &lt;strong>strategy on slides&lt;/strong> and &lt;strong>delivery in the wild&lt;/strong>. You inherit conflicting priorities, stale &lt;a href="https://www.projectmanager.com/blog/raid-log-use-one" target="_blank">RAID&lt;/a> logs, and steering committees that want clarity in twenty minutes. AI does not replace your accountability to sponsors—but it can shrink the hours you spend &lt;strong>reading, structuring, and drafting&lt;/strong> so you spend more time on &lt;strong>tradeoffs, people, and commitments&lt;/strong>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>